</head><body><table width="400" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><a name="TOP" id="TOP"></a><img src="Images/Help.gif" alt="" width="22" height="22" /></td><td bgcolor="#336DCC" width="100%"><div align="center"><span class="style1">phpPetitionScript Mail Configuuration Help</span></div></td><td><img src="Images/Help.gif" alt="Help" width="22" height="22" /></td></tr></table><table width="400" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2" align="center" valign="top" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><span class="style4"><a name="FromEmail" id="FromEmail"></a>FromEmail</span>:</td><td><p class="style2">The email that goes out to all signers asking them to confirm thier signature, the email address you put here shows them whom the email is from and if they reply it will also go to this address. </p><p class="style5"><a href="help.php#TOP">TOP</a></p></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#F3F3F3"><td colspan="2" align="center" valign="top" class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><span class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><a name="FromName" id="FromName"></a></span>FromName:</td><td><p class="style2">The same email described above that goes out to all signers asking them to confirm thier signature, the name you put here shows them whom the email is from</p><p class="style2"><span class="style5"><a href="help.php#TOP">TOP</a></span></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" align="center" valign="top" class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><span class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><a name="Subject" id="Subject"></a></span>Subject:</td><td><p class="style2">This should be self explanitory </p><p class="style2"><span class="style5"><a href="help.php#TOP">TOP</a></span></p></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#F3F3F3"><td colspan="2" align="center" valign="top" class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><span class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><a name="EmailServer" id="EmailServer"></a></span>EmailServer:</td><td class="style2"><p>If your email server is on the same server as this script you can use 127.0.0.1 or you can use localhost (which is the same IP address). If your email server is not on this server then you can use either the IP address but we suggest you use the email servers name, somehting like mail.YourDomainName.com (this name is just a sample do not use this exact name) </p><p><span class="style5"><a href="help.php#TOP">TOP</a></span></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" align="center" valign="top" class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><span class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><a name="SMTPAuth" id="SMTPAuth"></a></span>SMTPAuth:</td><td class="style2"><p>Turn &quot;On&quot; this option if you have to authenticate to send email. Some email servers that are on the same server as this script likely would not require this, but spam is such a problem, do not be suprised if this is required, Call you ISP to be sure. </p><p><span class="style5"><a href="help.php#TOP">TOP</a></span></p></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#F3F3F3"><td colspan="2" align="center" valign="top" class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><span class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><a name="Username" id="Username"></a></span>Username:</td><td class="style2"><p>This could get tricky because sometimes a username is actually your full email address. It can also be just a name. If you are unsure call your ISP to make sure </p><p><span class="style5"><a href="help.php#TOP">TOP</a></span></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" align="center" valign="middle" class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><span class="style4" style="border-right:thin #000066 dotted"><a name="Password" id="Password"></a></span>Password:</td><td class="style2"><p>We can not help you here only you know what your password is... at least that's what we hope ;) </p><p><span class="style5"><a href="help.php#TOP">TOP</a></span></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#336DCC">&nbsp;</td></tr></table></body></html>